CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781444875
OL,3,C'Liquid gold' plasma treatment helps
OL,4,Cparalysed man walk out of hospital
OL,6,FIt damages the peripheral nerves, the
OL,7,Fnetwork that carries messages from the
OL,8,Fcentral nervous system around the body.
OL,10,FThe condition affects around 1,300
OL,11,Fpeople a year in the UK, with symptoms
OL,12,Fsuch as numbness, pins and needles and
OL,13,Fmuscle weakness developing rapidly.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G5/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31806
SC,0006
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781444875
OL,3,C'Liquid gold' plasma treatment helps
OL,4,Cparalysed man walk out of hospital
OL,6,FFollowing his diagnosis, Mr Newitt was
OL,7,Ftransferred to a neurological ward at
OL,8,FUniversity Hospitals Coventry and
OL,9,FWarwickshire NHS Trust, where he had
OL,10,Ftwo key treatments ` intravenous
OL,11,Fimmunoglobulin (IVIG) and therapeutic
OL,12,Fplasma exchange, both of which are
OL,13,Fderived from donated plasma.
OL,15,FMr Newitt said: "There were times when
OL,16,FI honestly thought that my grandchild
OL,17,Fwas going to be my replacement."
OL,19,FOver 10 days, Mr Newitt had five IVIG
OL,20,Finfusions and five plasma exchanges.
OL,26,@wD@QOU
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G6/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
OL,23,TppppppppppppppppppGsource: itv.com/news
OL,24,ANext Page BNat News CNat TV FClean Feed
FL,319,300,200,140,000,100
PN,31807
SC,0007
CT,2,C
PS,c008
OL,0,        ECIMSBWebfax 1   F318A1781444875
OL,3,C'Liquid gold' plasma treatment helps
OL,4,Cparalysed man walk out of hospital
OL,6,FHis symptoms stabilised within days,
OL,7,Fand he was able to begin extensive
OL,8,Fphysiotherapy.
OL,10,FDespite being told it was unlikely he
OL,11,Fwould ever walk again, Mr Newitt
OL,12,Fwalked out of Leamington Rehab
OL,13,FHospital in October.
OL,15,FMr Newitt now exercises daily at home
OL,16,Fand in April was able to go on his
OL,17,Ffirst family holiday abroad in three
OL,18,Fyears.
OL,20,FHe and Ms Marshall are now urging more
OL,21,Fpeople to consider donating plasma.
OL,1,W~k4~sj5j5~s1G                    G7/10
OL,2,W/*%+,"-/.!,.!T,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,,
